'''Plinkart''' is a [[mobile phone application]] designed to identify works of [[art]], created by Mark Cummins and James Philbin.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.psfk.com/2010/04/mobile-app-recognizes-artwork.html|title=Mobile App Recognizes Artwork - PSFK|date=2010-04-26|work=PSFK|access-date=2018-07-31|language=en-US}}</ref>  Cummins and Philbin were one of three winners of the Education/Reference category of the [[Google]] ADC2 ([[Android Developer Challenge]] 2)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://code.google.com/android/adc/gallery_winners.html |title=ADC 2 Overall Winners |publisher=Google |accessdate=April 28, 2010}}</ref> where the pair won $100,000. PlinkArt was acquired by [[Google]] in April 2010.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/google/7582684/Google-buys-UK-search-engine-PlinkArt.html|title=Google buys UK search engine PlinkArt|last=Neate|first=Rupert|date=2010-04-12|access-date=2018-07-31|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref>

